.

 This is a study 24-week, two arm, double blinded randomized clinical trial to evaluate the effects of high-dose vitamin D3 supplementation compared with placebo, on activity disease, fatigue and bone mass.

 Sixty JoSLE patients will be randomized to receive placebo or vitamin D3 (50.

000 IU/week) for 24weeks.

 The patients return to visits in week 12 and week 24 for evaluation.

 Study will record clinical history, drugs in use, disease activity, and bone mass parameters.

